It is an Infrastructure as Code (IaC).
It support both type of languages JSON or YAML file is called as template.
A template is a JSON or YAML file that contains configuration information about the AWS resources you want to include in the stack.
Every stack is based on a template.
The template can be store in S3 by enabling an S3 Versioning.
When template upload, automatically the template will store in S3, incase the template is in S3 specify the S3 URL.
The template is called as stack in CloudFormation.

[Stack]
By using a single AWS CloudFormation template deploy to an target AWS account within an single AWS Region.

[StackSets]
By using a single AWS CloudFormation template deploy to an multiple AWS accounts across multiple AWS Regions.
